				The below post is my response to one of the many threads complaining about the new ads. <br>  <br> ---- <br>  <br> Go straight to  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://www.webwasher.com/">http://www.webwasher.com/</a>  do not pass go do not encounter hideous, laggy, banners full of screen hogging advertisements and popup adverts.  <br>  <br> I believe in advertising but the second performance takes a shit or popups start showing up webwasher gets turned back on. Needless to say it is running again <img src="/images/faces/wink.gif" border=0 alt="wink.gif" height=18 hspace=0 width=18 vspace=0> .  <br>  <br> ---- <br>  <br> I do not have a problem with advertising and understand why it needs to be there. I even click on them, on occasion, when visiting a website I like to pick up their hit count. However three of your little ad campaigns have caused me to flip on ww. The Zedo ads, that stupid freaking bunny and now this. The other two times I shutdown ww when the problem was cleared up and I will turn it off again when this one is but not until then. <br>  <br> The sidebar banners, or 'tower ads' as I have seen them called, take up too much of the working area in the forums. This is magnified if you use a lower resolution or have multiple, nonmaximized, windows up. Afew up top and on the bottom would seem to serve the same purpose without alienating the userbase you have. These boards beat the crap outa anything else out there and have a loyal userbase, don't destroy that by ruining the format. <br>  <br> Just my 2py, take it or leave it, thanks for listening.
